        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Bromley Kent</placeName>
                    <date>Tuesday</date>
                    <salute>My dear Owen</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am very anxious to have to have ten minutes talk with you, chiefly about the mammifers of the Plata,<ref target="#foot.f2"/> &amp; will call on you on Thursday morning at about ten oclock, if you will excuse so early an hour. If you <hi rend="underline">cannot</hi> see me, perhaps you w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> be so kind as to send me a line to save me trouble to, “7 Park St Grosvenor Sq<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>”</p>
<p>I have commenced your British Fossils<ref target="#foot.f3"/> with very great interest</p>
<p>Most truly yours | C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.2 on Thursday] ‘on’ <hi rend="italic">over</hi> <hi rend="italic">illeg</hi></note>
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.4 save me] ‘me’ <hi rend="italic">interl</hi></note>
                </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The conjectured date is based on CD’s record of having finished reading Owen’s <hi rend="italic">British fossil mammals</hi> (R. Owen 1846c) on 9 May 1846 (DAR 119; <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_8010.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Vorzimmer 1977</ref>, p. 135) and on a visit to London recorded in CD’s Account Book (Down House MS) on Thursday, 23 April.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD may have sought the interview to go over his summary of ‘Localities within the region of the Pampas where great bones have been found’ (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7343.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">South America</hi></ref>, pp. 106–7). See also <ref target="./DCP-LETT-968.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from G. R. Waterhouse, [30 March 1846]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">R. Owen 1846c. CD’s annotated copy is in the Darwin Library–CUL.</note>
        </div>        
            
